  "text": "An early observation of an underplated layer beneath a sedimentary basin was made at the Valencia Trough in the western Mediterranean Sea. [CITATION_1] find indications for relatively thick (up-to 8 km) underplate in the form of a series of subhorizontal reflectors on a length scale of 3-5 km. This underplate in the Valencia Trough mainly exists below the weakly stretched part of the continental crust, whereas the underplated layer is significantly thinner below the areas which have been moderately stretched, and it is absent at a weakly reflective Moho at high stretching factors. This tectonic sequence of variable stretching may be related to post-underplate stretching of the thinnest crust.",
